<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Duron:
[B]My guild was in hate all week, and I was there all weekend. We were only clearing to the maestro and to do Inny, due to the terrible pathing and stuck pet bugs, that lead to many camp outs and CR sessions.

In that time, to the best of my knowledge, the armour drops were:

Enchanter legs
Indo gloves, helm and boots and a bracer
Cleric legs x2, BP, Boots and arms
Shaman Bp
Bard bracer, boots
No mage or rogue drops

This was from a full WEEK of working the zone. Now this may have been a bit better if we had the time and resources to clear all the class specific mob houses, but with the way the zone stands now, that is incredibly difficult. I am not even sure that clearing the whole zone would have yielded much more. Clearly the wandering mob drops have been nerfed beyond reason. 

The only good point was that in taking the maestro down 4 or 5 times, he was not too stingy. The last time he was duel wielding six note blades, so there are some happy bards at least  :)

Duron[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
